    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b8605516_49995b25",
        "filename": "util/fuchsia/koid_utilities.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 63,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-27T16:21:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have ObjCCast\u003c\u003e and ObjCCastStrict\u003c\u003e in base for macOS, to provide a C++-ish way to deal with the distinct Objective-C type system in dynamic_cast-like way. (The Strict variant CHECKs instead of returning 0 if the types are wrong.) Do you think that something like that would be welcome in libzx?",
      "revId": "2c132d7a01354082196f45c676652e8fd2d2463f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ee17fcd5_53fe423c",
        "filename": "util/fuchsia/koid_utilities.cc",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 63,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001385
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-30T19:53:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "libzx is intended to be as thin a C++ wrapper around the syscalls as possible, and as such is \"un-opinionated\". Stuff like checked cast helpers would likely not fit in libzx, but perhaps in a higher-level, opinionated library. For our purposes we could add something in //base (and so in mini_chromium) for this purpose.",
      "parentUuid": "b8605516_49995b25",
      "revId": "2c132d7a01354082196f45c676652e8fd2d2463f",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
